value.0: <StartCheck>[Singing]</Start> A trip o'er the bridge might be... death for some folks... but danger is this hero's best friend.
And resting might be grand... but it won't save the boy child... from those awful drow... so save that kid if you know how.
Monster's grow bold as... heroes get old... and we all lose our strength in the end.
So make as much cash... while you're still young and brash...
Cuz danger is a hero's best... danger is a hero's best... danger is a hero's best friend.
<StartCheck>[Singing]</Start> There was a <boy/girl>... a very strange, enchanted <boy/girl>.
Oh a hero has... such sharp blades, dear... and he keeps them... keen and bright.
Just his wits has... old Amion Galie, dear... and he keeps them... way out of sight.
When that hero attacks... with his blades, dear... scarlet stains, they begin to spread...
Fancy gatekey... has ol' Amion here... so he'll open the door, though you may end up dead.
<StartCheck>[Singing]</Start> Standing here... guarding the bridge... I look over and I see you.
You cannot... go this way... until Seeker finds you true.
Good luck... it might be tough... but if you're in your prime...
Soon enough... you'll go through... time after time.
Flashback... the last guy... who even tried...
Found his guts on the ground... and then he died.
Why you be singing?
Who you be?
Why are you singing?
Who are you?
Um, this be good one. You keep singing.
This be stupid waste of time. You open door now.
That fun song, but me gotta go. You open door, please?
Oh, I love this one. Keep singing please.
Don't be stupid. Cut the singing and open that door for me.
Catchy tune, but I gotta get going. Want to open that door, please?
Fine, me go find Seeker.
You let me past, now!
Fine, I'll go talk to Seeker.
Let me through, or else.
